#!CSeaGreen #!N  #!Rvpeanot Adding Annotation to a 
Visual Program #!N #!EC #!N #!N You can also add annotation 
directly to the canvas. Select the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add Annotation option #!EF 
from the Edit pull-down menu. A cursor appears. Click on the 
canvas where you would like to place annotation. You can modify 
the text in the annotation by double-clicking on the annotation. A 
text-entry dialog appears. #!N #!N By default, the annotation text is 
visible on the canvas. You can choose the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Hide Text 
#!EF option on the text-entry dialog, in which case only a 
"marker" appears on the canvas. #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic 
#!EF #!N #!N  #!Lvpepage,dxall356 h Creating pages in the VPE  #!EL  #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   #!N 
